Jaws vertically aligned, mouth terminal. Premaxillary teeth in two rows, outer with 3*(13) or 4(22) tricuspid teeth, inner with five tri- to pentacuspid teeth. Maxilla reaching vertical through anterior fourth of orbit, with 2(14), 3*(17), or 4(1) unito tricuspid teeth. Dentary with three pentacuspid teeth, followed by smaller tricuspid and series of 5-10 small conical teeth decreasing gradually in size (
Fig. 2
).
